{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"18682d27-e615-4c06-b9a8-526421b24754","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n**1. In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n- **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n- **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (replaces the old framework + adapter + test SDK)\n- **Update** the target framework (MSTest v3 requires at least `net6.0` or `net462`—yours is fine)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net462</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThe `MSTest` meta-package bundles:\n- `MSTest.TestFramework` (attributes & assertions)\n- `MSTest.TestAdapter` (test discovery/execution)\n- `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (test host)\n\n**2. In `OrderServiceTests.cs`:** No changes needed—the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace and attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, `Assert.*`) are all preserved in MSTest v3.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f3c1531d-c965-4755-82d3-74d7c58c343c","outputTokens":349,"requestId":"9827:180764:3F6EF2:52E07E:69FFF052"},"id":"4ae5f7b0-bd78-4773-ad03-3531b33211d1","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:41:30.420Z","parentId":"b08ad1fe-6fcd-453e-a650-f1d9f2ce5cf7"}
